  "description": "HAD-MEEG is a multimodal neuroimaging dataset combining magnetoencephalography (MEG) and electroencephalography (EEG) recordings from 30 participants viewing 21,600 video clips across 180 human action categories. Recorded with identical stimuli and participants as the previously released HAD-fMRI dataset, HAD-MEEG provides millisecond-level temporal resolution to complement fMRI's spatial precision, enabling comprehensive investigation of spatiotemporal neural dynamics underlying human action recognition and social cognition.",
  "methods_description": "MEG and EEG were recorded from 30 participants during passive viewing of video clips depicting human actions. The stimulus set comprised 21,600 video clips spanning 180 action categories, identical to those used in the HAD-fMRI dataset to enable cross-modal integration.",
